{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "01", "M": "42", "S": "19"}}, "news": [{"title": "Noida International Airport to begin commercial operations from June 15", "para": "Noida International Airport (NIA) in Jewar will commence commercial flight operations on June 15, 2026, with IndiGo operating the inaugural flight. Akasa Air and Air India Express are slated to follow soon after. The airport, developed by YIAPL, will initially handle 1.2 crore passengers annually, with plans for significant expansion.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/noida-international-airport-set-to-launch-commercial-flights-on-june-15-2026/130680802?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-826545/130680802.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Telangana HC pulls up HYDRAA over illegal construction in Salkam Cheruvu FTL area", "para": "The Telangana High Court has sharply questioned HYDRAA's failure to act against the Barrister Fatima Owaisi Educational Campus. The institution is allegedly built in the Full Tank Level area of Salkam Cheruvu without proper approvals. The court ordered a detailed inquiry into officials who neglected their duties. Students' safety was also a concern raised by the judge.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/telangana-high-court-takes-action-against-illegal-construction-in-salkam-cheruvu/130680004?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1967773/130680004.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Goa's town planning department proposes to tag 28.4 lakh sq meter as \u2018non-developable\u2019", "para": "Goa's Town and Country Planning department is proposing to designate vast land tracts as non-developable. This move aims to protect significant natural areas. Three major parcels in Bardez and Pernem, covering over 28 lakh square meters, are included. These proposals are now open for public objections. This marks a shift from previous land use policies.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/goa-proposes-284-lakh-sq-meters-as-non-developable-areas-to-protect-natural-land/130680353?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-240321/130680353.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}